data.content:
user	user_region
data relationship, geographic association
The 'user_region' table connects geographic information to specific users through the user ID foreign key.

article	user
authorship, content creation<SEP>authorship, content generation
The 'article' table links articles to users who authored them using the user ID foreign key.<SEP>The article is associated with a specific user who created it, thus establishing authorship.

jing_du	user_region
geographic data, location identification
The 'jing_du' field provides the longitudinal data of the user's location within the 'user_region' table.

user_region	wei_du
geographic data, location identification
The 'wei_du' field provides the latitudinal data of the user's location within the 'user_region' table.

province	user_region
geographic classification, regional context
The 'province' field helps categorize the user's geographic area within the 'user_region' table.

city	user_region
geographic classification, urban context
The 'city' field specifies the urban locale of the user, enhancing the geographic data's granularity.

district	user_region
geographic classification, administrative context
The 'district' field further refines the user's location within the 'user_region' table, providing detailed geographic information.

article	click_num
engagement metrics, user interaction
The 'click_num' field indicates user engagement with the article by tracking views.

article	disagree
content reception, user feedback
The 'disagree' field shows how many users contested the article's content, reflecting reader reception.

article	pdatetime
publication timing, content relevance
The 'pdatetime' field associates the article with its publication time, relevant for chronological context.
